
[1]tavern-keeper

   TAV'ERN-KEEPER, n. One who keeps a tavern. In the United States, one
   who is licensed to sell liquors to be drank in his house, and to
   entertain travelers and lodgers, together with the horses or oxen
   composing their teams. Taverners are by law to be provided with
   suitable beds for their guests, and with fodder for horses and cattle.
